        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What if I spilled water into the control area of my PRD486?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "That's a known failure pattern — the PRD486 has the ignitor board, oven lock motor, and simmer control stacked under the top panel, and water from overflow cleaning can short any of them. Turn off the gas at the shutoff and the power at the breaker immediately. Don't try to run the range again until we've pulled the top and dried everything out. Depending on what shorted, you're looking at ignitor board ($285), oven lock motor ($225), or simmer board ($420) — sometimes all three. Moisture damage is covered under most homeowner insurance if the spill was accidental."
        }
      }
    ]
  }
];
