      <h2>A Pro Grand is a twelve-thousand-dollar piece of engineering. We respect that.</h2>
      <p>A Thermador Pro Grand 48" dual-fuel range lives in a lot of LA kitchens we've been inside — Bel Air, Beverly Hills, Brentwood, Pacific Palisades, Malibu, Calabasas, the foothills around La Cañada and Pasadena. These ranges cost between $11,000 and $14,500 installed. The standard response from Thermador corporate is a 5-day dispatch window through a Factory-Certified contractor. Most of our Pro Grand calls are people who can't wait five days for a working stove — a dinner party Saturday, kids at home, a kitchen that's the heart of a house.</p>
      <p>We run a different model. Factory-trained on the BSH platforms (Thermador, Bosch, and Gaggenau share the same parent and the same service architecture), parts for Pro Grand on the truck, average arrival inside four hours of the call. If we can't fix it the first trip — usually a deep control board or compressor-adjacent issue — we tell you that on the phone, not after the diagnostic.</p>
